{
  "doc_id": "56287",
  "text": "The metabolism of NP is complex and yields a wide array of metabolites, thus decreasing the relative amounts of NP in the test urine samples. In fact, only 10% of ingested NP is excreted in the urine as NP or conjugated NP [CITATION_1] . Therefore, currently available data on exposure levels inferred from the measurement of NP in urine samples may represent only a small fraction of the NP that actually constitutes exposure. Moreover, given the known bioaccumulative effects of NP, the potential influence on dendritic cell function in vivo is likely to be greater.",
